[SN]TITLE[SN]
Flooding incidents at Powys and Glynneath, fire service says

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Flash flooding has affected parts of mid and west Wales, the fire service has said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The A40 in Powys was closed for a short time after a heavy downpour during a thunderstorm washed stones and debris on the road at Trecastle between Llandovery and Sennybridge.
Four fire crews are also dealing with several flooding problems in the Glynneath area.
A weather warning is in force for south, west and mid Wales until 23:00.
Mid and West Wales Fire and Rescue Service said it was responding to incidents in the Glynneath area at High Street, Maes Yr Eglwys and the Dinas Rock Hotel.
